text:
Hey Louise, please meet Lauren your incredible E-Mentor we've been telling you about :smile:.  Feel free to introduce yourselves, say a little bit about what you would like to get out of the mentorship and continue chatting within this channel. :wave:

I will now be leaving the channel, but please direct message myself or penny-prospela if you have any questions. All the best for now! :slightly_smiling_face:

Hi Louise! It’s very nice to e-meet you! I look forward to mentoring you for the foreseeable future! It would be great to kick off with a bit of an intro. 
I understand you’re currently at University, is that right? What are you studying and how are you finding it? When are you graduating?

Hi, looking forward to learning so much from you too! I’m currently completing my Integrated masters. Although we’ve had some artistic work to complete, it’s been mostly been business oriented . Learning about how to start a business within the games/VFX industries, and how to maintain it. Although my undergrad degree was predominantly Vfx, this year I decided to learn more about the games industry which is why I opted to work on a pc game which we are currently developing. Although I enjoy the artistic side of all I’ve learnt, I want my career to veer more into the production side. Finally I’m graduating after May . Hope this gives you a clear understanding of my situation :slightly_smiling_face:

Wow! That’s amazing! That must be very intense, too! Where are you studying? I definitely think that having had a good understanding of the creative side will benefit you in a Production-based role, for sure. Perhaps we should start with some goals. What are your short-term (3-6 months) goals, and what are your long-term (1-5 year) goals? You can let me know as many of these goals if you like, we can hone them and change them as we go!
